-120618849.text: "Using a rapamycin resistant but kinase-active mTOR mutant (S2035T, mTOR-T) or kinase-dead mTOR-T mutant (S2035T and D2357E, mTOR-TE), we found that expression of mTOR-T, but not mTOR-TE, conferred resistance to rapamycin 's inhibition of Cd induced phosphorylation of S6K1 and 4E-BP1, as well as cell death, implying the preventive effect of rapamycin on Cd induced neurotoxicity is mTOR kinase activity dependent."
